<HEADLINE>
BACK TO THE STORE 
A NEW MODEL  
 A DATE IN COURT  
 SAY IT AGAIN 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Texas, Mass., Ohio)  (nk) 
 BY JAMES BARRON with JOE BRESCIA   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Marvin Traub, ringmaster of the circus known as Bloomingdale's
for 13 years before, during and after the department-store takeover
wars, is trying again. He has been named chairman of a new chain
that will sell furniture and bedding in outlet malls.
</P>
<P>
   He did not need a Rolodex of contacts to make the arrangements.
He is a director of Prime Retail, the largest owner of outlet
malls. And Financo, the investment banking firm where he has worked
since 1993, arranged the financing for the new company, Home
Company-Fine Furniture Direct.
</P>
<P>
   The first store is scheduled to open in May in San Marcos,
Texas, a long way from Italy and France, where Traub, 73, spent
last week attending to another of his ventures, a consulting
business. ``I've been having a very good time'' since leaving
Bloomingdale's in 1991, he said. ``I think that if you stop, you
get much older.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A NEW MODEL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Some cosmetics makers are advancing the idea that models come in
all shapes, sizes and ages. Last month, Evonne Swann, 61, who
claims to be the oldest woman to sign a beauty contract, began
appearing in ads for Oil of Olay moisturizer.
</P>
<P>
   Now, Revlon has signed Emme, a plus-size model, which means size
12 and above. ``This gig is a big deal,'' she said. ``For so many
years, so many women put themselves through hell thinking if they
don't look like a 16-year-old, they're not beautiful. I kind of
finish that off, the idea that we're all included in beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A DATE IN COURT  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A first date ``turn-on'' would be ``a nice kiss good night,''
Ryan Martin, a 22-year-old club manager, told Cosmopolitan magazine
when he was selected for a special issue on America's ``most
wanted'' single men.
</P>
<P>
   That was in June. Last month, Ryan was arrested on charges of
drugging and raping a 23-year-old woman in Worcester, Mass. He
pleaded not guilty and was released on $20,000 bond.
</P>
<P>
   Detective Lt. William O'Connor of the Worcester police said that
Martin met two women in a bar and took them to a restaurant he
managed after it had closed. He said that Martin served them
alcoholic drinks, followed by a cupful of a liquid Martin said had
come from a nutrition store.
</P>
<P>
   The woman Ryan is accused of raping ``felt very tired, was
unable to drive her car home and that's when they were offered a
stay at Martin's house,'' the lieutenant said. ``The next morning
the victim woke up and, thinking she may have been sexually
assaulted, went to the hospital.''
</P>
<P>
   O'Connor said that hospital personnel examined her for evidence
of rape. The woman was found to have gamma-hydroxybutyrate, which
O'Connor said was a so-called date rape drug, in her bloodstream.
</P>
<P>
   Martin's lawyer, Anthony Salerno, said that Martin denied
serving such a substance. He added, ``I don't think he's
acknowledging that there was even any sex.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SAY IT AGAIN  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   So what does Max Weinberg, the drummer in Bruce Springsteen's E
Street Band, have to say about the fact that the Rock and Roll Hall
of Fame nominated Springsteen but not the band?
</P>
<P>
   With a straight face Weinberg said, ``No one deserves to be
included in the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame more than Bruce.''
</P>
<P>
   No hard feelings?
</P>
<P>
   With a straighter face, he said, ``Like I said, no one deserves
to be included in the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame more than Bruce.''
</P>
<P>
   Would he and the band perform for, or with, Springsteen at the
induction ceremony?
</P>
<P>
   ``Like I said, no one deserves to be included in the Rock and
Roll Hall of Fame more than Bruce.''
</P>
<P>
   Doesn't this sound like a broken record?
</P>
<P>
   He laughed, and walked away.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
