waterlogged trees, tossed into the Caribbean by a hurricane, have
apparently sailed 200 miles from Guadaloupe to Anguilla, scientists
reported. Their report has wowed a community of scientists that has
been arguing since early in this century about whether such
journeys were even remotely possible, let alone observable. By
Carol Kaesuk Yoon.
