brought home by the demise last week of Isaac Mizrahi's business, a
tale that is being mourned and dissected here by designers, editors
and retailers alike. What is evident in the wake of Mizrahi's
closing of his business is that designers in their own houses are
ships at sea, unable to surf the choppy fashion waters unless
tethered to a bigger boat _ like Tom Ford at Gucci, Narciso
Rodriguez at LVMH, John Bartlett at Byblos and the newcomers
Veronique Branquinho and Raf Simons, who showed their first
collection here for Ruffo, a large Italian leather company. By
