<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DDN-MACK-BENGALS09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Speed means success for Bengals' Mack
 &HT;    By Marty Williams
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI _ Being able to run fast is a valuable asset for a
kickoff return man, but it's just as important to know when to run
fast.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you return kicks, you're just like a running back,'' said
Cincinnati's Tremain Mack. ``You wait for the blockers to do their
jobs, you read the holes and when the holes open, you take off.''
</P>
<P>
   Mack took off for a 97-yard TD in the Bengals' last game at
Baltimore and will be trying to add to his stats this Sunday when
the Bengals host Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   Mack, who ranks fifth in the NFL with his 28.4-yard average,
said returning kicks doesn't involve much cerebral exercise. ``You
just catch the ball and run hard. If the hole opens up, you take
it. If it doesn't open up, you try to find another one. If that
doesn't work, you just try to get as many yards as you can.''
</P>
<P>
   Special teams captain Eric Bieniemy usually is Mack's lead
blocker. ``A good return is all about spacing and timing. The
return man has to be patient, he has to have a knack for knowing
when everything is set up and when to make his move. Tremain has
the knack.''
</P>
<P>
   Mack, the Bengals' fourth-round pick in the 1997 draft, set a
school record for kickoff return yards in a season with 514 as a
redshirt junior at Miami (Fla.).
</P>
<P>
   Mack had only 13 tries in '97, but had 39.5 yards per return.
``We had a really good defense and I didn't get many chances,'' he
said. ``I didn't get my first return until the sixth game.''
</P>
<P>
   He had been on the return team the previous season, but did
nothing but block and grow increasingly more frustrated.
</P>
<P>
   ``The next year, I kind of suggested at a meeting that if I
wasn't going to be the return guy, I didn't want to be on the
(return) team. The reason was that I was tired of blocking for guys
who weren't running as hard as I thought they should.''
</P>
<P>
   That memory has helped shape Mack's aggressive running style.
``I want the guys in front of me to know that I'm going to run hard
no matter how tired I am or what the circumstances are. That every
time I touch the ball, I think I'm going to score. When they know
that, they tend to block a little harder.''
</P>
<P>
   No Bengal has ever led the NFL or the AFC in kickoff returns.
Willie Shelby holds the club record with a 25.4-yard average in
1976.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
