<HEADER>
A6133 &Cx1f; sci-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HEALTH-FITNESS-ADVISO     10-08 0420
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEALTH-FITNESS-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Expanded Health and Fitness Coverage in ScienceTimes &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Editors, attention science, health, features editors.
</P>
<P>
   Beginning Monday, Oct. 12, The New York Times News Service will
increase its coverage of health and fitness. The increase reflects
The Times's seven-coumn expansion of its Tuesday Science Times
section.
</P>
<P>
   This new section-within-a-section, about 12 columns in all, will
take as its purview stories and standing features in the following
areas:
</P>
<P>
   _ General medical features with a practical orientation
</P>
<P>
   _ Nutrition and diet
</P>
<P>
   _ Fitness, including features for novices
</P>
<P>
   _ The healthcare system from a patient's point of view
</P>
<P>
   _ Behavior, including child-rearing.
</P>
<P>
   These stories will be listed under a separate heading, HEALTH &AMP;
FITNESS, in the SCIENCE-TIMES-BUDGET on Monday afternoons.
</P>
<P>
   Among the columns and standard features will be the every-week
BRODY-HEALTH, The Personal Health column by Jane E. Brody.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, these standard features will move on an occasional
basis:
</P>
<P>
   SCI-FITNESS-NOVICE _ Various fitness programs (rock climbing,
rowing, etc.) from a beginner's point of view.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-FIT-BODIES _ Short: How particular regimens affect the body.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-HEALTH-NOSTRUMS _ Short: Traditional health wisdom in the
light of modern research.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-HEALTH-PRO&AMP;CON _ Short: Two experts with opposing views on a
health question.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-HEALTH-RX-MONEY _ Short: Help with getting the most from
your health dollar.
</P>
<P>
   And every week:
</P>
<P>
   SCI-VITAL-SIGNS (Undated) _ Shorts on health and fitness.
</P>
<P>
   The space alloted to The Times's coverage of science and the
environment will remain the same, about 25 columns in Science Times
on Tuesdays and space as needed throughout the week.
</P>
<P>
   All Science stories, including the new material, will have a
slugline of the form BC-SCI-SLUG-NYT and carry an ``a'' general
news category code for newsroom computer sorting.
</P>
<P>
   Also, the weekly computer column will move from ScienceTimes to
the Circuits section on Thursday. Written by Peter H. Lewis, it
will be filed Wednesday afternoon with the slug
CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TEXT QUESTIONS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Gary E. McCardell, the day supervisor (e-mail,
garymc(at)nytimes.com).
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (888) 346-9867
</P>
