   AUTHORS-BERG (Undated) _ Interview with A. Scott Berg, author of
a new biography of Charles Lindbergh.
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LIMITS (Undated) _ ``Without Limits,'' the latest film
biography of Oregon long-distance runner Steve Prefontaine,
features strong performances, running sequences are gripping (even
when you know the outcome), and many of the scenes sparkle with the
celebrated Towne wit and subtext. Still, it fails to be a great
sports drama.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-MONUMENT (Undated) _ ``Monument Ave.'' is the latest ``Mean
Streets'' clone, is an unappetizing compilation of regurgitated
moments from other, better movies.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-HOLYMAN (Undated) _ Eddie Murphy continues to ride his
recent success wave with ``Holy Man.'' It's a better-than-average
comedy that actually has a lot to say about how we live (or how we
think we should live).
</P>
<P>
   By Paula Nechak. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
