<P>
   TROOPER-SUICIDE (Boston) _ William Johnson, 50, a highly
decorated Massachusetts state trooper, was a spit-and-polish cop
whose brilliant career was derailed, he believed, by a fateful
encounter with mobster-turned-informant James ``Whitey'' Bulger.
His effort to reclaim his reputation ended when he took out his
handgun and killed himself. By Thomas Farragher. (2 takes)
