<P>
   HOUSE-IMPEACH (Washington) _ The House votes 258-176 to
authorize a historic impeachment investigation into President
Clinton's role in the White House sex scandal and its aftermath. It
is the third time in U.S. history that the House has voted for an
impeachment inquiry. By DAN FREEDMAN and JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-DEMOCRATS (Washington) _ Thirty-one Democrats bolted from
their party and joined the majority Republicans in authorizing an
impeachment investigation against President Clinton. We take a look
at who these lawmakers are and why they defected. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-SHUTDOWN (Washington) _ White House and congressional
leaders say progress is on several budget-related issues that need
to be worked out. With the House and Senate closing in on
adjournment, lawmakers are likely to pass a stopgap measure that
would fund government agencies and allow the negotiations to
continue. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   GAYS-ADS (Washington) _ Gay rights groups protest a new
conservative TV ad campaign that says gays and lesbians can change
their sexual orientation through immersion in the Christian faith.
The gay groups say evidence of such change is only anecdotal and
that efforts to change can be psychologically harmful. By ERIC
ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   MORDUE (Washington) _ Norman Mordue, a state Supreme Sourt
justice from Onondaga County, N.Y., wins Senate Judiciary Committee
approval to become a federal judge for the northern district of New
York. His nomination now moves goes to the full Senate. By MARK
HELM. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLENN-NASA (Cape Canaveral) _ Sen. John Glenn, D-Ohio, and six
other astronauts discuss preparations for the upcoming launch of
shuttle Discovery. Glenn, 77, is scheduled to return to space for
the first time since he orbited the Earth in a Mercury capsule in
1962. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-AL (Cleveland) _ The Cleveland Indians have been to the
World Series two of the past three years and are the reigning
American League champions. They are appearing in their third AL
Championship Series in the past four years, yet they were given
little or no chance against the mighty New York Yankees. They
return home tied 1-1 against the Yankees. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-NL (Atlanta) _ The San Diego Padres will try to take a 2-0
lead over the Atlanta Braves in Game 2 of the National League
Championship Series. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
