   AUTO-REVIEW-BOS (Undated) _ The BMW M Coupe is the latest
manifestation of the Z3, with 240-horsepower I-6, five-speed manual
gearbox, a tin top and a square back. By John R. White.
</P>
<P>
   CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN-TEX (Undated) _ Confidential to all of you
who are considering a compact sport-utility: If you want one that
has as much utility as it has sport, a true sport-ute rather than
just sport-cute, you'll want to check out the all-new Suzuki Grand
Vitara. OK, it is a stupid name, but you have to get beyond that.
It was picked by Suzuki officials in Japan, and they probably had
no idea that it sounds rather silly in English. By G. Chambers
Williams III.
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-LEXUS-TOYOTA (Undated) _ Did conspicuous consumption
disappear with the 1980s? Not where large, expensive sport
utilities are concerned. Indeed, it seems, the bigger and more
expensive the luxury sport utility, the better it sells. Consider
the case of the Lexus LX 470 and its virtually identical cousin,
the Toyota Land Cruiser. Both full-sized sport utilities, priced
between $46,500 and $57,000, were redesigned and introduced in
April. Toyota had predicted the less expensive Land Cruiser would
outsell the LX 470. Instead, sales of the pricier LX 470 has
exceeded sales of the Land Cruiser in some months this year. By
Michelle Krebs. With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-CARS-COX (Undated) _ Warning: Reading beyond this point
could be expensive. By Douglas Kalajian.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-CARS-GADGETS-COX (Undated) _ Tired of trying to watch the
kids and the road at the same time? Let them watch TV. By Douglas
Kalajian.
</P>
