<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PERSONAL-FINANCE-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
 ATTENTION: Managing editors, business editors, weekend editors 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service calls your attention to the
following personal finance stories moved during the last week.
</P>
<P>
   For retransmissions of these stories, please call 888-346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INVESTING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MUTUAL-FUNDS-BLOOM (Boston) _ A shareholder of Fidelity
Investments' mutual funds filed a lawsuit alleging the funds'
boards weren't independent enough to act properly as ``watchdogs''
for investors. By Tim Quinson.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-OIL-STOCKS-NYT (Undated) _ Money managers and analysts
have called the bottom on the great oil collapse of 1998. Now they
are buying into oil services stocks. By Agis Salpukas. With
Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIGHT-Q&AMP;A-NYT (Undated) _ A question-and-answer session
with a market insider. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
