</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ For some reason, cop movies lend themselves to some of
the most generic titles in cinema. We've already had, in large
black block letters on white backgrounds, ``Cop,'' ``Cop &AMP; 1/2,''
``Cops and Robbers'' and ``One Good Cop.'' Now ``One Tough Cop''
joins them on the shelf. Eventually, Meryl Streep will star in
``One True Cop,'' and we can all be done with it. You might think
that a bad title doesn't necessarily mean a bad movie. In the case
of ``One Tough Cop,'' you would be wrong. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story
has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
