<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    IMAGE, Etcetera Magazine sponsor gay-lesbian film fest
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   IMAGE Film &AMP; Video Center and Etcetera Magazine present this
weekend of features and short films as part of Out on Film '98:
Atlanta's 11th Annual Gay &AMP; Lesbian Film Festival.
</P>
<P>
   TONIGHT
</P>
<P>
   -- 8 p.m.: ``Some Prefer Cake,'' a comedy about a friendship
between two women, one gay, one straight.
</P>
<P>
   -- 10 p.m.: ``Fun in Boy's Shorts,'' an omnibus of short films
about gay men, including ``Horse Dreams in BBQ Country,'' ``Your
Kiss,'' ``Fruit Machine,'' ``Cupid,'' ``Boy Next Door,'' ``SPF
2000'' and ``Sink or Swim.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Midnight: ``Surrender Dorothy,'' Kevin DiNovis' black
comedy-drama about the psychosexual games played between a heroin
addict and a friend who makes him dress as a woman in exchange for
drugs.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- 11 a.m.: ``Armistead Maupin's More Tales of the City,'' the
first three episodes of the Showtime TV series.
</P>
<P>
   -- 2 p.m.: ``The Real Ellen Story,'' a behind-the-scenes
documentary about Ellen DeGeneres and the coming-out episode of her
sitcom. Shown with the short documentary ``Helping Ellen Out,''
including interviews with Bryn Mawr students on the night of the
famous ``Ellen'' episode.
</P>
<P>
   -- 4 p.m.: ``The Human Race,'' a feature documentary about nine
HIV-positive men who sailed the 1997 TransPacific Yacht Race.
</P>
<P>
   -- 6 p.m.: ``Party Monster,'' a documentary about New York
``club kid'' Michael Alig and his arrest for murder. Shown with the
short ``Wonder Woman: Battle of the Basher.''
</P>
<P>
   -- 8 p.m.: ``Sticky Fingers of Time,'' a sci-fi feature about a
woman time-traveling from 1953 to New York's East Village in 1997.
Shown with the short film ``Wavelengths.''
</P>
<P>
   -- 10 p.m.: ``Hard,'' a police thriller about a rookie cop who
becomes the target of a serial killer of gay men.
</P>
<P>
   -- Midnight: ``Leather Jacket Love Story,'' concerning the
romance between an 18-year-old would-be poet and a blue-collar boy.
</P>
<P>
   -- Midnight: ``Erotica: A Journey Into Female Sexuality,''
featuring interviews with female artists and writers known for
their eroticism. With ``Savor Me (Sabor a Mi).''
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- 11 a.m.: ``Armistead Maupin's More Tales of the City,'' the
final three episodes of the Showtime series.
</P>
<P>
   -- 2 p.m.: ``Out of the Past,'' a documentary chronicling the
gay and lesbian stories that have been left out of American history
books.
</P>
<P>
   -- 4 p.m.: ``Love Story,'' a documentary following the affair of
a lesbian couple in wartime Nazi Germany.
</P>
<P>
   -- 6 p.m.: ``Dyke Delights: New Lesbian Shorts,'' including
``Scent uVa Butch,'' ``It Happened in the Stacks,'' ``Breakfast
With Gus,'' ``The Ever-Elusive Lesbian'' and ``Uhuru.''
</P>
<P>
   -- 8 p.m.: ``Like It Is,'' the drama about the love affair
between a tough Blackpool boy and a slick London pop music
producer; co-starring Roger Daltrey.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
