<P>
   SUICIDE _ DAY 1
</P>
<P>
   SUICIDE _ With the National Suicide Prevention Conference
opening this week, the AJC takes a human look at the devastatingly
complex series of problems that can result in suicide, and what
Georgians are doing to combat the problem. (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SUICIDE-INTERVENTION _ When the National Suicide Prevention
Conference meets in Nevada this week, the first lesson will be that
suicide isn't so much a problem as a matrix of problems.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no single one-size-fits-all answer,'' says Mark
Rosenberg of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, one of
the conference's sponsors. ``Different subgroups have different
needs. What you do for impulsive teenagers is different from what
you do for chronically depressed older people. We have to develop
different interventions.'' (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   SUICIDE-HISTORY _ Famous suicides in history. (Auchmutey,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   SUICIDE-RHETA _ Rheta Grimsley Johnson on the suicide of a man
she loved. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WITH GRAPHICS _ THE GEOGRAPHY OF SUICIDE and THE GENDER OF
SUICIDE, by Stephen Camper
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO _ PEACHTREE, N.C. _ The Barnett family of Peachtree,
N.C., harvests burley tobacco as they have for generations, on one
of the small tobacco farms that were once common throughout much of
the South. Randy Barnett, 45, principal at the local elementary
school, has been doing this long enough to see public opinion of
his crop wither. ``Fifteen years ago, people were real proud of
their tobacco,'' he says. ``And now,'' he shakes his head. ``People
think you are like a drug dealer. The kids at school think its a
bad thing.'' (Harmon, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 45. WITH
PHOTOS and PAGE LAYOUTS.
</P>
<P>
   FOWLER _ Savannah food writer Damon Lee Fowler was trained as an
architect but has become an irascible food maven in the tradition
of his mentors Marcella Hazan, Karen Hess and John Fowler. We visit
him at his Savannah home to see what's cooking. (Brock. Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILYSIZE _ Is one child too few? Are three too many? We'll
talk to families about the perfect family size and what they
considered in making that decision. A couple with 1 child likely to
say they have focus on the quality of life and being able to do
things. A couple with three or more children will tell you that
they feel robbed of personal time. We'll get the pros and cons from
a familiy with one child, another family with three kids and a
third family with five or more kids. (Ricardo, Austin
American-Statesman). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   STYLE
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-BIGKIDS _ You think you have problems finding clothes.
What if you're a size 12 and you're only 12 years old? Parents with
children who are developed beyond their age face special problems
when buying clothes for their kids (mostly girls). How to find
stylish clothing that fits them AND still have their kid look like
a kid. (Hill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12-15. WITH PHOTOS and
LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-BIGKIDS -TIPS _ Sidebar on what to look for when shopping.
(Hill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 5-7.
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-BIGKIDS -SHOP _ Sidebar on where to buy (stores, specialty
shops) and . (Hill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 5-7.
</P>
