<P>
   RAC-BAMAGANG _ In the 1980s, the Alabama Gang graduated from the
dirt tracks in the state of Alabama to rule NASCAR and, in some
respects, Talladega. Bobby and Donnie Allison, Red Farmer and the
young guns, Davey Allison and Neil Bonnett, were favorites nearly
every week. Then tragedy hit. Neil Bonnett and Davey Allison were
killed; Bobby Allison suffered severe head injuries in a wreck, and
the small racing town of Hueytown, Ala., never was the same. For
years, people in the state tried unsuccessfully to carry on the
tradition. And now, the Allisons and Farmer remain connected to
racing, but at a few steps below the big-time. (Levine, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
