<P>
   SCUBA-DIVING _ Scuba diving, once thought of as dangerous sport
only for the most adventurous outdoorsperson, is becoming safer
every year. Now, nearly anybody can dive, and many are, judging by
the increase in participants. And the sport also is becoming more
family-oriented; even daycare is provided by some dive packages.
The industry also is considering lowering the minumum age to be
certified from 12 to 10. (Bernarde, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
WITH PHOTO
</P>
