   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- Oct. 8, 1998 -- NY-STOCK-EXCHANGES, 10-8 --
Officials are working to keep the three top stock exchanges in
lower Manhattan. The search for new homes for the financial
industry has become a high-stakes, real estate version of musical
chairs, as the New York, American and Nasdaq Stock Exchanges, which
are also being wooed by New Jersey, try to extract subsidy packages
and New York developers maneuver to get a piece of the business.
(Ruby Washington/New York Times Photo)
