When it came time Thursday for the House to vote on an impeachment
inquiry drafted by Democrats, with a deadline and limited scope,
every Republican opposed the measure. Except Rep. Jay Dickey of
Arkansas, a three-term conservative. Dickey, explained his support
for the Democratic option as a matter of conscience, principle and
independence. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
