Auctioneers selling fish at the Tokyo Central Wholesale Market,
where the stakes can be just as high as at Sotheby's. Or, at least,
they used to be. As Japan muddles through its recession, even
sushi, the ultimate Japanese gastronomical obsession, is taking a
bite. Next to rice, fish is perhaps Japan's most basic foodstuff,
and the decline in fish sales has paralleled the nation's economic
slump. (Indira Lakshaman/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
