From left, Erin Quinn Purcell, Derin Basden and Gregory Jackson in
``Duet! A Romantic Fable.'' ``Duet!'' spins wittily and nattily
from one vignette to the next, parodying the conventions of the
dating game. As much as it's intended to poke fun at modern
romance, ``Duet!'' supplies a funny, running commentary on modern
entertainment. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
