<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOSTER ADJUSTS TO LIFE WITHOUT LEWIS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ There has been no change in his practice routine,
no change in his attitude and no change in his performance.
</P>
<P>
   But when he arrives at the team hotel tonight in Tucson, things
will no longer be the same for Bruins tailback DeShaun Foster.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jermaine's my roommate on road trips, and this will be my
first time without him,'' Foster said.
</P>
<P>
   Foster won't have fellow tailback Jermaine Lewis on the sideline
Saturday night when the No. 3 Bruins face No.10 Arizona, either.
Lewis is serving an indefinite suspension for fighting.
</P>
<P>
   Junior Keith Brown will start in Lewis' absence, but the Bruins
are counting on a major contribution from Foster, the talented true
freshman who gained 185 all-purpose yards last week against
Washington State.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's getting better every day,'' UCLA coach Bob Toledo said.
``He's learning the offense and understanding defenses.''
</P>
<P>
   The concern with Foster, as with all freshman tailbacks in
hostile environments, is fumbling. Arizona plays an attacking,
physical style and figures to swat and poke at the ball when it's
in Foster's hands.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to tell DeShaun to be confident, and beg him not
to fumble,'' Bruins guard Andy Meyers quipped.
</P>
<P>
   Unimpressed: Arizona cornerback Chris McAlister has not been
impressed with UCLA quarterback Cade McNown this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``He looks like an average quarterback to me, personally,''
McAlister told Tucson reports. ``I haven't seen anything special
about him.''
</P>
<P>
   Payday: Pac-10 athletic directors agreed to give UCLA its
television compensation (approximately $507,000) for the canceled
game at Miami. There has been no decision on rescheduling for Dec.
5.
</P>
<P>
   Stat of the Week I: UCLA has lost four consecutive games in
Tucson. In those defeats, the Bruins have rushed for 227 yards
while Arizona has run for an astounding 1,064.
</P>
<P>
   Stat of the Week II: USA Today did a midseason calculation of
the top teams based on the Bowl Championship Series formula. If the
season ended today, Ohio State (No. 1) and Nebraska (No. 2) would
play for the national championship in the Fiesta Bowl. UCLA is
third.
</P>
<P>
   Review of the Week: All-American offensive tackle Kris Farris is
a film buff who has agreed to review a movie each week for the
Daily News. This week: ANTZ.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dreamworks' newest film, `ANTZ,' deserves a trip to the
theater. Not only is the computer animation superb, but the
screenplay is packed with high-brow comedy. Woody Allen voices `Z,'
the neurotic ant who finally dares to `think for himself.'
</P>
<P>
   ``I must confess I had little interest in seeing this film _
mainly due to its unappealing ad campaign _ but it wasn't long
before `ANTZ' captured my attention. It's the perfect family film,
one that will entertain both kids and adults.'' three pancakes (out
of four).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-08-98 2325EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
