<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS EXPECTING PANTHERS TO HAVE ATTITUDE ADJUSTMENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The only change the Cowboys expect out of the
Carolina Panthers in Sunday's matchup after the shocking
quarterback switch from Kerry Collins to Steve Beuerlein will be
one of attitude.
</P>
<P>
   Though his staff has just begun looking at videotape of
Beuerlein at quarterback, Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said the
Panthers' offense will not be that much different with the former
Cowboys backup at the controls.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey, however, does expect the Panthers (0-4) to use the
change as a rallying point in attempt to get their first victory.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys fullback Daryl Johnston agrees.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rumors have gone around since Kerry made his announcement that
the guys have rallied around Steve,'' Johnston said. ``That's going
to be a big plus for them.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnston said the Panthers don't have to worry about Beuerlein,
who played with the Cowboys in 1991 and 1992, quitting on them as
Collins did. Collins walked into coach Dom Capers' office Wednesday
and said he wanted to be removed from the starting lineup because
his heart wasn't in it.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's one of the most competitive people I've ever been
around,'' Johnston said of Beuerlein. ``He doesn't like to lose at
anything, whether it's a football game on Sunday or a golf game on
a Saturday afternoon in the off-season.''
</P>
<P>
   Beuerlein, who started his career with the Raiders, played a key
role in the Cowboys' rise to prominence in the '90s. He replaced an
injured Troy Aikman at the end of the 1991 season, won four
consecutive games and led the Cowboys to the playoffs for the first
time since 1985. The Cowboys lost in the second round to the
Detroit Lions, but Beuerlein set the table for the 1992
championship team.
</P>
<P>
   He signed a free-agent contract with the Cardinals in 1993, and
the Panthers made him the first pick of the 1995 expansion draft.
He has backed up Collins ever since, going 3-1 in spot duty as a
starter in 1996 and was 1-2 last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'll mean a lot to him coming back to Dallas,'' Johnston
said. ``He has a house here; his family lives here in the
off-season. This is the place he really got a good start to his
career. So, it'll be a big game for him personally.'' &QL; 
READY FOR BLITZ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Instead of playing mostly zone coverage behind the blitz, Capers
asks his defensive backs to play more man-to-man coverage.
</P>
<P>
   The way opponents have tried to attack this plan is by spreading
the field, employing four- and five-wide receiver sets. The
advantage, Cowboys quarterback Jason Garrett said, is that the
Panthers have to limit the amount of people they send at the
quarterback. The disadvantage is that the offense is left with
fewer people to protect the quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   ``They are not your typical defense,'' Garrett said. ``We'll
have to recognize where their guys are coming from.'' &QL; 
HE SAID IT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Teams ought to start going for it on fourth down.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Cowboys punt returner Deion Sanders, who said teams lose field
position when they punt away from him and they chance a big return
when they punt to him. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Staff writer Kevin Lyons contributed to this report.  &QL;
</P>
